<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 24 at 2:37PM MDT until May 24 at 3:30PM MDT by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN LEA COUNTY...
At 237 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles west of
McDonald, or 11 miles southwest of Tatum, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
McDonald.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
